            <StackPanel x:Key="LaunchHelpToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Launch the help content in a browser window.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AltTextToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is the tooltip text that will display when the cursor hovers over the image.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Add, edit or delete an Algo Start asset from the database.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="QuestionToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Add, edit or delete a Question asset from the database.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				The same Question can be used in any number of Algorithms, and can be used multiple times in a given algorithm.  When edited will change wherever it is used.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Add, edit or delete an Answer asset from the database.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				The same Answer can be attached to any number of Questions, in any number of Algorithms, and can be used multiple times in a given algorithm.  When edited will change wherever it is used.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Add, edit or delete a Conclusion asset from the database.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				A Conclusion can be used as a summary of an analysis, a recommendation, a call to action, a point of information, or as meta-data to be used in further analysis. The same Conclusion can be attached to any number of Algorithms, and can be used multiple times in a given algorithm.  When edited will change wherever it is used.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="BulletToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Add, edit or delete a bullet from the database.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Bullets are usually instructions that are attached to conclusions. The same Bullet can be attached to any number of conclusions, and when edited will change wherever it is used.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="TimesToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				In some Algorithms the conclusions need to be displayed in order of priority, which is set by the Conclusion Sub-Category (with ties managed by Category priority). Due to the need to assign and prioritise Sub-Categories across different Categories, one needs to add Conclusion Sub-Categories in a separate place (under this Conclusion Sub Category icon) before assigning them to Categories.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="GroupsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				View groups and group children from the database.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Groups are collections of criteria or codes that form a descreet piece of data for a give member. Group membership is calculated prior to traversal runtime.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ContainsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				When searching for assets the “Contains” function will find all assets that contain the search term in any field.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				The search is not case sensitive.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="StartsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				When searching for assets the “Starts” function will find all assets that start with the search term in any field (e.g. Expert, Summary, Explanation).
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				The search is not case sensitive.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="EndsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				When searching for assets the “Ends” function will find all assets that end with the search term in any field (e.g. Expert, Summary, Explanation). Note that if there is a punctuation mark at the end this needs to be included in the search.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				The search is not case sensitive.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="EqualsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				When searching for assets the “Equals” function will find all assets that contain the exact search exclusively in any field, with no other text, punctuation or spaces. Note that if there is a punctuation mark at the end this needs to be included in the search.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				The search is not case sensitive.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="CutToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Cut (Ctrl + X). Cut the selection and put it on the clipboard.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="CopyToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Copy (Ctrl + C). Copy the selection and put it on the clipboard
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="PasteToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Paste (Ctrl + V). Paste the contents of the clipboard
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="InsertToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The Insert function allows the user to insert a hyperlink, video from you Tube or a picture into any field of an asset that is displayed to the user. Display is dependent on the coding in the UI.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: You must first put your cursor in the place where you want to insert something.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="WebServiceToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is the web service URL used to connect to the database.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				This should be the same Web Service URL that is used in the Visio Logic Builder under “Settings”.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="UserNameToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Rules controlling username requirements are set by your database administrators.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="PasswordToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Rules controlling password requirements are set by your database administrators.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="PermissionsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>Users are created with one of the following levels of permission:</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Reviewer</Run> – A reviewer can only view the builder and the various assets (“read only”).</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Editor</Run> - An editor can edit the text of assets but cannot add, delete or move assets or library labels.</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Builder</Run> – A builder is able to add, delete and edit assets and manage library functionality as appropriate.</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Admin</Run> – An admin user has full algorithm management rights i.e. they are able to run SQL scripts as well as delete algorithms that have been exported from Visio into the database.</TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>If access level needs to be changed, this must be done through the database/system administrator.</TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ChangeWebServiceToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Choose a different web service to point to a specific database.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ShowDisabledToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Shows disabled fields for different asset types.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="EnablePriorityChangesToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Allows you to change the order of Category 1 and Sub Category items, by using the green and red arrows.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AllowAutoSaveToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Enabling AutoSave puts the system into edit mode.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Any changes you make to an asset will automatically be saved when you move off that asset unless you click “Cancel”. This allows you to make a series of changes to multiple assets without clicking on Edit and Save after each change.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="PromptforCommentsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				If the prompt for comments is enabled, then  you will need to confirm the type of change made each time you hit the save button.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="EnableSpellCheckToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Spell checks the asset fields.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="EnableValidationToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Validates any instances where natural language has been used. Should the natural language syntax be incorrect, then you will not be allowed to save the amendment.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="UpdateDerivedAssetsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Updates any derived assets, having made an update to an asset.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="UpdateApplicationToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Updates the application to the most up to date version if applicable.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoManagementToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Allows scripting &amp; deletion of loaded algorithms and scripting of individual assets.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Also contains the reporting functionality.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="GenerateScriptToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Upon selecting an algo from the list, click the generate script button in order to generate an SQL script for the algorithm that allows deployment to other environments.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: This script will contain all the asset and category changes needed to support the algo.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SaveScriptToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Saves the script generated to a desired location of your choice, which can later be deployed to another environment i.e. Test or Production.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SelectReachableAlgosToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Having highlighted an algorithm, and selecting the “Selected reachable algos” button; this will display all algorithms physically connected with it.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="RefreshListToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Refreshes the current list of algorithms promoted to the database in order to display any real time updates made.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="DeleteSelectedAlgosToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Deletes the selected algo from the database.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="UserNameColumnToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Lists the username of the individual loading the algorithm.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="TitleColumnToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Lists the title of the algorithm.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="PromotedColumnToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Specifies the date and time the algorithm was promoted to the database.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="EditTranslationToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Edits the translation of the asset.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ShowTranslationToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Having selected the asset type, enter the translation language into the text box i.e. Spanish and click on Show translation. This will display the translated text within the builder.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="TranslationLanguageToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Enter in the language to be used for translation. Please note that the next time you login, the language entered will appear in the dropdown list.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AddLanguageToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Add a language to the drop down list.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="RemoveLanguageToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Delete language from dropdown.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="RedGreenArrowToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Click on ‘Enable Priority Changes’ in order to enable the green and red arrows, which will allow changing the order of Category 1 and Sub Category items.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AddButtonToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Add a record.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="DeleteButtonToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Delete currently selected record.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ClearButtonToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Clear selection.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="EditButtonToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Edit / rename entry.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ListButtonToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Creates a list.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Allows to create multiple assets in one go rather than creating them separately.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="DataSetToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				In the Asset Builder, individual Assets of all types live within one of many Author-created/Author-named domains called “data sets”. While an Author can use Assets from multiple data sets to create an individual logic pathway, that is unusual; most often, an Author will supplement topic specific assets from one specific data set (for example, the “medical/social” data set) with general Assets from the “Generic” data set.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="Category1ToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Each individual Asset is linked to an Author-created and Author-ordered entry in each of these windows; that linkage instructs the Virtual Expert Toolkit how to display/format/label individual Assets when they are included within a Summary Document created at the end of a traversal.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SubCategoryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Each individual Asset is linked to an Author-created and Author-ordered entry in each of these windows; that linkage instructs the Virtual Expert Toolkit how to display/format/label individual Assets when they are included within a Summary Document created at the end of a traversal.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="Category2ToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Each individual Asset is linked to an Author-created entry in this window; this linkage serves as an index of the Asset facilitating its retrieval from the universe of Assets in the Builder’s Library.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AssetsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Lists all the assets created within a particular dataset.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SearchToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Type any text to search the asset database for that text.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				Searches can be modified in a number of ways
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Algo</Run> – To restrict the search to a specific algo (Syntax - Algo:&lt;ID&gt;).</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Algo</Run> – To restrict the search to a group of algos (Syntax - Algo:&lt;ID1&gt;[*],&lt;ID2&gt;[*][,...]). You can use '*' after the AlgoID to search all reachable algos from that AlgoID.</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Question</Run> –  To restrict the search to assets that use a specific question (Syntax - Question:&lt;ID&gt;).<LineBreak/>Available in Algos and Answers.</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Answer</Run> – To restrict the search to assets that use a specific answers (Syntax - Answer:&lt;ID&gt;).<LineBreak/>Available in Algos and Questions.</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Conclusion</Run> – To restrict the search to assets that use a specific Conclusion (Syntax - Conclusion:&lt;ID&gt;).<LineBreak/>Available in Algos and Bullets.</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Bullet</Run> – To restrict the search to assets that use a specific Bullet (Syntax - Bullet:&lt;ID&gt;).<LineBreak/>Available in Algos and Conclusions.</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Date</Run> – To restrict the search to assets that have been edited after a certain date (Syntax - Date:&lt;Date&gt;).</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">User</Run> – To restrict the search to assets that have been edited by a specific user (Syntax - User:&lt;Username&gt;).</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Type</Run> – To restrict the search to assets of a specific type or multiple types separated by commas (Syntax - Type:&lt;AssetType&gt;[,...]).</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	<Run FontWeight="Bold">Order</Run> – Assets are ordered alphabetically. The assets can be ordered by ID by order:id</TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				Examples
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				To search for all question assets that contain the word 'test' and are used in algo id 160 and are used with answer id 1.
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock FontStyle="Italic">
				test Algo:160 Answer:1
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				To find conclusions that contain the word 'colour' and are used algo id 3594 or any reachable algo from algo id 3580.
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock FontStyle="Italic">
				Algo:3580*,3594 colour
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				To search for all answers last edited by user 'dave' since January 2013.
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock FontStyle="Italic">
				User:dave Date:2013-01-01
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				Integer parameter also support negation by prefixing the value with a minus. So to search for all assets that are in algo id 1 but not in algo id 2.
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock FontStyle="Italic">
				Algo:1,-2
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note : Search clauses, seperated by a space, can be combined. However, repeating a clause is not valid.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="CancelListToolTip">
