				Opens this asset for editing.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnCloseToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Closes the asset page.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnUsageToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Displays the instances of where the asset has been used.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnRefreshToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Updates the page with any updates.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnDeleteToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Deletes the current asset.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnDuplicateToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Clones the current asset and opens the new instance for editing.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnDeriveAnswerToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				For Table-row Questions, User Entry Questions, Calculated Questions or Conclusions, one can create an answer that will reflect this asset in the Algorithms.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnDeriveQuestionToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				For User Entry or Calculated Questions, one can create a question that is used to retrieve the value for use in making decisions on that value. For example, for a question calculating BMI (body mass index), if you wish to sort people into BMI categories, you must use a derived question to retrieve the BMI value. To access the derived question once it is created, right click on the original question and click on “Open question node”.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnCreateAnswerToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Creates an answer to be used for multiple categories as well as the use of single answer questions. In order to find the new answer node asset, right click on the original asset in the asset list and select ‘Open Copied Answer’.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnCancelToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Clicking the “Cancel” button will abort the editing, and return the Asset to its prior state in all respects.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnSaveToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Saves the asset to the database.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnFindToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Finds and/or replaces any text within the asset fields.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnNLWToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The wizard generates the natural language syntax, having specified any necessary parameters.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Pick an assessment type from the drop down list.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoAgesToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Age range in years.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Format: {xxx-xxxy}
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoNameToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Name of the algorithm. This will in evidently appear as a title on the top of the page throughout the traversal.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoKeywordsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				List any keywords separated by commas, which can later be used to search the algorithm based on what has been entered. The key word search functionality will need to have been written on the front end of the system, in order for the keyword search functionality to work as appropriate.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoReferencesToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is currently an unused field, please ask Expert-24 for further information.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoDestinationToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is currently an unused field, please ask Expert-24 for further information.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoWordMerge1ToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is used as part of a sentence after the “after with” clause, which will be displayed as part of the summary.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoWordMerge2ToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is used as part of a sentence after the “Problem name”, which will be displayed as part of the summary.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoLastReviewDateToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is the date the last time an algo was updated.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				This is a manual field.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="QuestionExpertToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is the text that will appear in the Asset window of the Builder as the Asset’s “name” and that will appear on the graphical representation of the Asset on the Visio grid. It is written in the (expert) language of the Author. (e.g. “myocardial infarction”) and is usually a positive statement derived from/reflecting the question.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Once an asset has been used in a Production database, the essence of the asset, as defined by the “Expert” field, should not be changed or modified or reporting and data integrity will be compromised. Wording to the user can be changed as long as the essence of the “Expert” field remains intact.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="QuestionSummaryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is the text that will appear when the Question is summarized on a Summary Report at the end of the traversal.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="QuestionQuestionToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is the text that will appear in the UI when this Question Asset is reached during a traversal.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="QuestionExplanationToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Any text the Author places here will be available to the user during a traversal as a “pop-up window” accessed by clicking on an information icon.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				NOTE: The system automatically places this icon on the UI when the Author makes an entry into this field.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="QuestionBuilderInfoToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Information on the asset that is not shown to the user but may be helpful to the authors or editors of the asset.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="QuestionCommentsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				If it is desirable for a user to be able to enter comments to explain an answer, then this field can be set as per the list of drop down options.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="QuestionCounterToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is used in “Counter Set” questions only, which are used to indicate the beginning of the scoring of a set of answers. This should be set to 0 for all other questions. The standard “Counter set” question is also set to start the scoring at 0, but if for any reason one wishes to start the scoring at a higher number, a new counter set question is created and the number entered here.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="QuestionHistoryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The “History” type determines whether or not (and for how long) a question and its associated answers are stored in the person’s historical record for use in subsequent traversals.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				NOTE: The field defaults to “Transient”.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="TransientHistoryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The Question and its associated answers are retained ONLY during the current traversal (This means that the Answers obtained to the Question “used” again within the current traversal without re-asking the question).
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SemiPermanentHistoryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The question and answer are kept indefinitely or until deleted.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: this will eventually have an expiry date, as currently acts exactly the same way as a permanent question/answer.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="PermanentPositiveHistoryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				If the Answer is “Yes,” it is stored indefinitely or until deleted; if “No,” it is not stored.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				e.g. “Have you had your tonsils removed?”.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="PermanentHistoryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The question and answer are kept indefinitely or until deleted.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="TransientNoSummaryHistoryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The question and answer are not placed into a Summary document
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				e.g. the Author may choose not to display in the Summary Statement the message: “You will now be transferred to the Abdominal Pain algorithm, as this is a potentially more serious problem than your sore throat.”
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="TransientNoPreanswerHistoryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This question will be presented to the Author each time it appears in a traversal without an “if not,” because its meaning may be different in different settings within the logic
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				e.g. “Did you think this was the right thing to do?”
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Black" Margin="0,12,0,12" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				It can also be used when one might encounter the same question with different mixes of answer sets within the same traversal.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				e.g. which of the following symptoms are you experiencing?” could be associated with one set of answers in the Sore Throat algorithm and another following transfer to the Headache algorithm.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SemiPermanentNoSummaryHistoryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The question and answer are kept indefinitely or until deleted, but will not appear on the summary page.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SemiPermanentNoPreanswerHistoryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The question and answer are kept indefinitely or until deleted, but with no pre-answer.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="MandatoryPhotoCommentToolTip">
