                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="CalculatedTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Calculate an answer using numerical information known.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="CounterSetTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The question type is defined and created by the system. The question is found as a template in the Logic Builder and as defined and locked assets in the generic data set in the Asset Builder. New ones can be created if you do not want to count starting from 0.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="CounterCheckTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The question type is defined and created by the system. The question is found as a template in the Logic Builder and as defined and locked assets in the generic data set in the Asset Builder.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionCheckTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Conclusion check is a question that asks, “Have these conclusions already been reached during this assessment?” It is often used to make sure that everyone gets at least one conclusion when an assessment is complex.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="CalculatedQuestionCheckTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The question type is defined and created by the system. The question is found as a template in the Logic Builder and as defined and locked assets in the generic data set in the Asset Builder.  No template. Created by clicking on “create question” button in a calculated question asset.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="TableNonExclusiveTypeToolTip">
