            <StackPanel x:Key="TableExclusiveTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Tables where there is only one answer per row.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="FreetextTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Allows users to enter their answer into a free text field.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Depricated
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="GenderCheckTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The question type is defined and created by the system. The question is found as a template in the Logic Builder and as defined and locked assets in the generic data set in the Asset Builder.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ImageQuestionTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Allows the answers to a 1 answer multiple choice question to be hot spots on an image, for example, “Where is the pain located?” with answers being hot spots on a body image.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="UserLanguageCheckTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Works like a conclusion check.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="CustomQuestionTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Future expansion.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="BasicdefinedTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is used if radio buttons are present, hence used for a single answer question.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="MultipleCategoryTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Most common type of answer. Alphanumeric text. Does not use “Greater or equal”, “Less than”, or “multiplier” fields. No calculations possible.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AgeTypeToolTip">
