                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="GenderTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The answer type is used for either a male or a female.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="BodypartTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is a basic defined answer type.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ValueSortTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Uses “Greater or equal”, “Less than”, and “Multiplier” fields. No calculations possible.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="DerivedfromconclusionTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Checks traversal history for a specific conclusion node. The answer is derived from a conclusion provided to the user.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="DerivedfromquestionTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Obtains a value from the derived question.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ValueCalculatedTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Uses Answer Text field for an equation. Acceptable range of answers can be set in the “Greater or equal” and “Less than” fields. Generates a single value from all derived questions.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ValueChooseTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Same as multiple category (example: “more than 2”).
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ValueEnterTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Text is just the units of the thing entered, as an entry box will be rendered with the units beside it.  Uses “Greater or equal”, “Less than”, and “multiplier” fields.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="TextEnterTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The answer type required is a free text entry field.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="DateEnterTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The answer type required is a date or time format field.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Use the drop-down arrow to choose the Answer type.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerStoreifNegativeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The “Store if negative” box has a tick as a default. This means that if this answer is presented but not chosen, then the summary will show.  If you wish only an answer that is chosen or selected to appear (positives, not negatives), then click on Edit, and un-tick this box.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: This prevents the user from checking their negative answers at the end, so this is generally not a good idea. The only time that answers will not show on the summary screen if “Store if Negative” is ticked, is if it is a >1 answer question with one or more generic “basic defined” answers, such as “Pending”, or “Unknown”.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerGreaterToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Sets the greater or equal field.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerLessToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Sets the less than field.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerMultiplierToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This sets the answer type to either weeks, months, years or leaves this set as normal.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerMinToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Sets the less than field.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerMaxToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				The default of &quot;0&quot; will allow text of almost any length to be added, as this is the unvalidated state, but the text entry box displayed will have a size of x characters. Setting the maximum number of characters to another integer will determine the size of the displayed text box.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerSetTextToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Sets the ‘Greater or equal’ and ‘Less than’ fields in the Expert field.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerExpertToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is the text that will appear in the Asset window of the Builder as the Asset’s “name” and that will appear on the graphical representation of the Asset on the Visio grid. It is written in the (expert) language of the Author.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				e.g. “myocardial infarction” is usually a positive statement derived from/reflecting the question.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerSummaryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is the text that will appear when the Answer is summarized on a Summary Report at the end of the traversal.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerAnswerToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is the text that will appear in the UI when this Answer Asset is reached during a traversal.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AnswerExplanationToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Any text the Author places here will be available to the user during a traversal as a “pop-up window” accessed by clicking on an information icon
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: The system automatically places this icon on the UI when the Author makes an entry into this field.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionInformationToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				If you wish a conclusion to come up under a particular heading on the Conclusions Screen, then you must tick the “Information” box on the conclusion window. The default is no tick.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionWatchoutToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This indicates that the conclusion is to be treated as a Watchout Condition.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionSelfCareToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This indicates that the conclusion is to be treated as a SelfCare action.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionSilentToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Silent conclusions are never seen by users but are used as pieces of logic in and of themselves. For example, if doing an insurance underwriting assessment, the conclusion may be reached that a person is high risk for a back pain claim. This may not be presented to the user, but would be used in determining whether to underwrite insurance, and at what cost.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				A conclusion is made silent by ticking the “Silent” box on the conclusion window (after going into “Edit”). The default is no tick.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionAgesToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Age range in years.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Format: {xxx-xxxy}
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionExpertToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is the text that will appear in the Asset window of the Builder as the Asset’s “name” and that will appear on the graphical representation of the Asset on the Visio grid. It is written in the (expert) language of the Author. (e.g. “myocardial infarction”) and is usually a positive statement derived from/reflecting the question.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Once an asset has been used in a Production database, the essence of the asset, as defined by the “Expert” field, should not be changed or modified or reporting and data integrity will be compromised. Wording to the user can be changed as long as the essence of the “Expert” field remains intact.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionSummaryToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is the text that will appear when the Conclusion is displayed on a Report at the end of the traversal.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionExplanationToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Any text the Author places here will be available to the user during a traversal as a “pop-up window” accessed by clicking on an information icon [NOTE: The system automatically places this icon on the UI when the Author makes an entry into this field.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionMoreDetailToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Additional text to be displayed as part of a conclusion. e.g. Medical References.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="BulletTextToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is the text that will appear in the bullet.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ShowBulletsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Displays a list of bullets used in the conclusion.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="HideBulletsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Collapses the screen so that all bullets used within the conclusion are hidden.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AddBulletsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Add Bullets to the conclusion.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="RemoveBulletToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Removes a bullet from the conclusion.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="RemoveAllBulletsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Removes all the bullets from this conclusion.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: This update is only applied after the conclusion is saved.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="MoveUpBulletToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Should there be multiple bullets present, then you can use the ‘Move Up’ icon to move a bullet up the list.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="MoveDownBulletToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Should there be multiple bullets present, then you can use the ‘Move Down’ icon to move a bullet down the list.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ShowSelectedOnlyToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Filters the list of algorithms to display, by only displaying those which have been selected via the “Select Reachable Algos” or that have been typed into the text box.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ScriptAssetsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Enables scripting of individual assets instead of full algorithms.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="CopyScriptToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Copies generated script to the local clipboard.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SelectAlgoTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Select an algorithm type to select all algorithms in the database of this type.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SpellCheckLanguageToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Please select the language type to be used.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: This is the language used to spell check the assets
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoTrackerToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Allows you to track the algorithm path in Visio.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="CheckOldReportToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This report allows checking the differences in the report since a specified date. The report does a merger between the date entered and today’s date and highlights the changes which were made between this timeframe.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionReportToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is a text report that contains all of the text in the conclusion assets found in the highlighted assessments, including all bullets.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ConclusionSummaryReportTypeToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is a text report that contains a summary of all of the conclusions found in the highlighted assessments.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="QuestionAnswerReportToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is a text report that contains all of the text in the question and answer assets found in the highlighted assessments.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SummaryTitleReportToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is a text report that contains all of the summary points that can be generated by this algorithm.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="EnableCategoryChangesToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				You will not be able to move an asset to another category, unless the “Enable Category Changes” is enabled.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AlgoReleaseProgressToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
                    This is a summary report that contains release status of the selected Algo(s).
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="MostPopularQuestionAnswerReportToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is a text report that contains the most popular Question and Answer Instances.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="MostPopularConclusionReportToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This is a text report that contains the most popular Conclusion Instances.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="OtherReportsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Custom reports can be set-up upon request.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Please speak to Expert-24 for further information.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AssetReportToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Report detailing asset content across a set of algorithms. If 'Show Translation' is on the report will generate content for the selected language either in a seperate column or merged into the base language.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				This report can be run with a different base language if required.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="RunNamedReportToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Custom reports can be set-up upon request.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Please speak to Expert-24 for further information.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AddTargetToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Add a target environment to the list
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="DeleteTargetToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Remove a target environment from the list
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="TargetToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				List of target environments.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: These environments need to be set up on the server by your system administrator.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ExportToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Upon selecting an algo(s) from the list, select a target environment and click the Export button in order to export the selected algorithm(s) to the target environment.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: if you wish to save the script for rollout to other environments use the generate script function.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="UsageToggleToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Toggle between "Algos", "Assets" and "Languages" to check the usage of assets in algos, within natural language in other assets or in translated content.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Algo Mode (default): This will display instances of where the selected assets have been used within algos.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Assets Mode: This will search the database for other assets that use this asset in natural language.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Languages Mode: This will list all the translations this asset is used in.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="QuickReportToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This generates a report based on all the assets that appear in the Assets column list.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="btnNaturalLanguageTesterToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Upon selecting the NL Tester button, you will be prompted to select the field for testing natural language.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ScriptWithoutAssetsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Upon selecting an algo from the list, click the script without assets button in order to generate an SQL script for the algorithm that allows deployment to other environments.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: This script will <Run FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="Red">NOT</Run> contain any asset or category changes that may be needed to support the algo.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ScriptXmlToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This retrieves just the Xml that represents the Visio portion of this algo. This can only be run on one algo.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: This is an administrator function. It can be used to generate a Visio document that represents the flow of the algo.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SearchTranslationToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				When enabled asset searching is performed on the translations of the assets and not in the original asset text.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: This may slow down searching considerably. Try searching within a specific algo (algo:xxxx) or asset categories to increase performance.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ccToolTip">
                <TextBlock Margin="0,0,0,6">
				You can insert text based on whether the respondent has previously reached a specific conclusion or not, using the syntax:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{cc + conclusion ID|Text you want to insert if that conclusion has previously been reached}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{cc9785|Unsure about use of medication} inserts the phrase “Unsure about use of medication” into the report at that point if conclusion 9785 has been reached. If the conclusion has not been reached, no text is displayed.
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6">
				You can also insert different alternative text based on the respondent arriving at one or more conclusions, using the syntax:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{cc + conclusion ID|Text if the conclusion is reached|Text if the conclusion is not reached}
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				As well as performing a single check on a single conclusion, you can also nest the conclusion checks, so that if one conclusion is true, the system checks that an additional conclusion has been reached and display text or another variable.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="tcToolTip">
                <TextBlock Margin="0,0,0,6">
				Resets Natural Language context to current Traversal
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{tc}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{tc} Ensures all question and conclusion based Natural Language clauses are processed in the contex of the current traversal
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				Note: The {tc} clause is only necessary when using the reciprocal {tp} clause and context is valid for the entire payload
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="tpToolTip">
                <TextBlock Margin="0,0,0,6">
				Sets the Natural Language context to a previous Traversal (if found)
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{tp[algoid[|algoid[+ ...]]]} 
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{tp} Ensures all question and conclusion based Natural Language clauses are processed in the contex of the previous traversal with the same start algoid
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{tp1234} Ensures all question and conclusion based Natural Language clauses are processed in the contex of the previous traversal started with algoid 1234
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{tp1234|2345|3456} Ensures all question and conclusion based Natural Language clauses are processed in the contex of the previous traversal started with either algoid 1234, 2345 or 3456
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				Note: The {tc} clause is used to reset the context back to the current traversal, context is consistent for the entire node
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="laToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				A comma-separated list with a final "And" is a list of items separated by a comma with an "and" separating the final two items, for example:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				You indicated that you are taking Drug A, Drug B and Drug E
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{la{qa1234}|{cc1234|text}|{item3}}
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				Where each item on the list is plain text or another natural language clause, for example {qa7777}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: The {qa...} syntax used with a multiple select question will output all answers from that question in the list.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="loToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				A comma-separated list with a final "Or" is a list of items separated by a comma with an "or" separating the final two items, for example:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				You indicated that you are taking Drug A, Drug B or Drug E
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{lo{qa1234}|{cc1234|text}|{item3}}
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				Where each item on the list is plain text or another natural language clause, for example {qa7777}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: The {qa...} syntax used with a multiple select question will output all answers from that question in the list.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="llToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				A linear list is a list of items separated by a comma, for example:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				You indicated that you are taking Drug A, Drug B, Drug E
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{ll{qa1234}|{cc1234|text}|{item3}}
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				Where each item on the list is plain text or another natural language clause, for example {qa7777}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: The {qa...} syntax used with a multiple select question will output all answers from that question in the list.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="lrToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				A list with hard returns is a list of items where each item begins on a new line, for example:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				You indicated that you are taking<LineBreak/>Drug A<LineBreak/>Drug B<LineBreak/>Drug E
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{lr{qa1234}|{cc1234|text}|{item3}}
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				Where each item on the list is plain text or another natural language clause, for example {qa7777}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: The {qa...} syntax used with a multiple select question will output all answers from that question in the list.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="lbToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				A bulleted list is a list of items where each item begins on a new line preceded by a bullet, for example:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				You indicated that you are taking
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	Drug A</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	Drug B</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	Drug E</TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{lb{qa1234}|{cc1234|text}|{item3}}
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				Where each item on the list is plain text or another natural language clause, for example {qa7777}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: The {qa...} syntax used with a multiple select question will output all answers from that question in the list.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="lnToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				An ordered list is a list of items where each item begins on a new line preceded by an ordered numeric, for example:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				You indicated that you are taking
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">1. Drug A</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">2. Drug B</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">3. Drug E</TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{ln{qa1234}|{cc1234|text}|{item3}}
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				Where each item on the list is plain text or another natural language clause, for example {qa7777}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock>
				Note: The {qa...} syntax used with a multiple select question will output all answers from that question in the list.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="qpToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				You can insert text based on the answer to a question using
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				{qp + question asset number|answer asset number|Text to display is true|Text to display if false}
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				For example {qp7777|1333|Correct} inserts the text 'Correct' if the question with asset ID 7777 is paired with the answer asset ID 1333. If the respondent did not choose answer 1333, no text is inserted.
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				You can also use this form of natural language to display alternative text based on the answer that the respondent supplies.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	{qp7777|1333|Text A|Text B} would insert 'Text A' if the respondent has chosen answer 1333 and 'Text B' if the respondent has not selected answer 1333.</TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="12,6,0,0">•	{qp7777|1235|Text A|{qp7777|6754|Text B}} would insert 'Text A' if the respondent has chosen answer 1235 and 'Text B' if the respondent has chosen answer 6754 and not answer 1235.</TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="caToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				To insert the lay statement of a conclusion, use the syntax:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				{ca + conclusion asset number}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{ca4562} inserts the lay statement of conclusion 4562 if it has been reached in the traversal. Empty string is inserted otherwise.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="qaToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				To insert the answer supplied to a single answer question, use the syntax:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				{qa + question asset number}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{qa2332} inserts the answer the respondent has given to single answer question asset 2332. If no answer is found empty string is inserted.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ceToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				To insert the explanation of a conclusion, use the syntax:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				{ce + conclusion asset number}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{ce4562} inserts the explanation of conclusion 4562 if it has been reached in the traversal. Empty string is inserted otherwise.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="qvToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				To insert the result of a previusly calculated value question, use the syntax:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				{qv + question asset number}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{qv8888} inserts the result of a value entry or calculated question with asset ID 8888.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="qsToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				To insert a respondent's answer given in response to a free text question, use the syntax:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				{qs + question asset number}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{qs5465} inserts the answer the respondent has given to the free text entry question with asset ID 5465.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="qdToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				To insert a respondent's answer given in response to a date entry question, use the syntax:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				{qd + question asset number}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{qd2323} inserts the date answer the respondent has given to the question with asset ID 2323.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="qtToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				To insert the results of a table question use the syntax:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				{qt + question asset number}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
				{qt8990} inserts and html table with the child questions and answers of the table question with the asset ID 8990.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="xxToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
                    To insert text based on gender, use the syntax:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
                    {xx + Text you want to insert if female}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
                    For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
                    {xxYou are female} inserts the phrase "You are female" if the gender is female.
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
                    {xxYou are female|You are not female} inserts the phrase "You are female" if the gender is female otherwise inserts the phrase "You are not female".
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="xyToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
                    To insert text based on gender, use the syntax:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
                    {xy + Text you want to insert if male}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
                    For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
                    {xyYou are male} inserts the phrase "You are male" if the gender is male.
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
                    {xyYou are male|You are not male} inserts the phrase "You are male" if the gender is male otherwise inserts the phrase "You are not male".
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="xzToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
                    To insert text based on gender, use the syntax:
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
                    {xz + Text you want to insert if neither male or female}
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
                    For example
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
                    {xzYou are neither male or female} inserts the phrase "You are neither male or female" if the gender is neither male or female.
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock>
                    {xzYou are neither male or female|You are either male or female} inserts the phrase "You are neither male or female" if the gender is neither male or female otherwise inserts the phrase "You are either male or female".
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ScriptForLanguageToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Scripting for language can be a dangerous thing to do, and should be done only by experienced users. This will replace all the native primary language text on the target system with the language text selected.
                </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0">
				This should only be done on systems which already has the primary language set to the secondary language on the source system.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold">
				If in any doubt DO NOT USE!
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="EnableHTMLValidationToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				This option validates the XHTML compliance by testing that all elements are closed and correctly formed.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="AddTableRowToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Adds an empty row to the table.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontStyle="Italic">
				Note: No changes are saved to the database until 'Save Changes' is exectued.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="DeleteTableRowToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Removes the selected row(s) from the table.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontStyle="Italic">
				Note: No changes are saved to the database until 'Save Changes' is exectued.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="InsertRowToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Inserts a row into the table with the same value in column one as the selected row.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontStyle="Italic">
				Note: No changes are saved to the database until 'Save Changes' is exectued.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="RefreshTableToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Refreshes contents of the grid and resets the sorting to default.
                </TextBlock>
                <Rectangle Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Stroke="Blue" Margin="0,6,0,6" StrokeThickness="1" />
                <TextBlock FontStyle="Italic">
				Note: Any pending changes are discarded and are not retrievable.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="CancelChangesToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Cancels any pending changes to the database and refreshes the table.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SaveChangesToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Saves any pending changes to the database and refreshes the table.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="SelectTableToolTip">
                <TextBlock>
				Loads the selected database table to the datagrid.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel x:Key="ScriptTableToolTip">
